rs]]<ref>{{cite web|title=The Amazing Meeting 5: Guest Biographies|url=http://www.randi.org/amazingmeeting/tam5/bios.html|accessdate=4 February 2012|url-status=bot: unknown|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120315182825/http://www.randi.org/amazingmeeting/tam5/bios.html|archivedate=15 March 2012}}</ref>\n|| 800<ref>{{cite web|title=Good News About Coffee And Amazing Skeptic Conference|url=http://www.scientificamerican.com/podcast/episode.cfm?id=511616D0-E7F2-99DF-3102FE2C4C454F5E|accessdate=15 February 2012|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120517120613/http://www.scientificamerican.com/podcast/episode.cfm?id=511616D0-E7F2-99DF-3102FE2C4C454F5E|archivedate=17 May 2012}}</ref>\n|-\n|January 25\u201327, 2008 ||Plantation Hotel & Conference Center, Plantation, FL ||TAM 5.5 ''Skepticism and Activism'' || [[Brian Dunning (author)|Brian Dunning]], Jeff Wagg, Mark Roberts, [[Phil Plait]], Alison Smith, [[James Randi]], [[Michael A. Stackpole|Michael Stackpole]], Bart Farkas, [[Martin Rundkvist]], [[Robert S. Lancaster|Robert Lancaster]], [[Rebecca Watson]], and Kelly Murphy Jolkowski<ref>{{cite web|title=TAM 5.5 Skepticism and Activism|url=http://www.randi.org/site/index.php/component/content/article/48.html|accessdate=4 February 2012}}</ref>||\n|-\n|June 19\u201322, 2008|| [[The Flamingo]] Paradise, NV ||TAM 6'' Skeptic - Modern Skepticism in the Internet Age''|| (Keynote) [[Neil DeGrasse Tyson]],<ref name=Shaw>{{cite book|last=Shaw|first=Charles E.|title=The Untold Stories of Excellence|year=2011|publisher=Xlibris Corporation|isbn=978-1-4628-8835-1|page=92}}{{Self-published inline|certain=yes|date=December 2017}}</ref> [[PZ Myers]], [[Richard Saunders (skeptic)|Richard Saunders]], [[Matthew Chapman (author)|Matthew Chapman]], [[Arthur T. Benjamin|Arthur Benjamin]], [[Steven Novella]], [[Ben Goldacre]], [[Tim Farley]] [[Ben Radford]], Jeff Wagg, [[Teller (magician)|Teller]], [[Richard Wiseman]], [[Phil Plait]], [[Michael Shermer]], [[Adam Savage]], [[George Hrab]], Alison Smith, [[Greydon Square]], [[Banachek]], [[Hal Bidlack]], [[James Randi]], Lee Graham, [[Penn Jillette]] and [[Sharon Begley]]<ref>{{cite web|title=TAM 6|url=http://www.randi.org/site/index.php/component/content/article/156.html|accessdate=4 February 2012|url-status=live|archiveurl=http://arquivo.pt/wayback/20090710083729/http%3A//www%2Erandi%2Eorg/site/index%2Ephp/component/content/article/156%2Ehtml|archivedate=10 July 2009}}</ref> || 900{{Citation needed|date=June 2015}}\n|-\n|July 9\u201312, 2009|| [[Southpoint Casino]], Enterprise, NV ||TAM 7|| (Keynote) [[Bill Prady]],<ref>{{citation|title=SC professor attends critical thinking conference|url=http://www.winfieldcourier.com/articles/2009/09/19/people/people/doc4ab4d17c5c2ed817655736.txt|date=September 19, 2009|newspaper=[[The Winfield Daily Courier]]|location=Winfield, Kansas|accessdate=February 7, 2012 }}</ref>[[D. J. Grothe]], [[Jennifer Ouellette]], Joseph A. Albietz III, [[Stephen Bauer]],  Chip Denman, [[Harriet A. Hall|Harriet Hall]], Ray Hall, [[George Hrab]], [[Ray Hyman]], Alison Smith, [[David Gorski]], [[Teller (magician)|Teller]], [[Brian Dunning (author)|Brian Dunning]], [[Tim Farley]], Christian Walters, [[Phil Plait]], [[Jamy Ian Swiss]], [[Rebecca Watson]], [[Steven Novella]], [[Adam Savage]], [[Banachek]], [[Michael Shermer]], Derek Bartholomaus, Johnny Thompson, Michael Goudeau, [[Mac King]], [[Penn Jillette]], Victor Isaac and Fintan Steele<ref>{{cite web|title=The Amaz!ng Meeting 7 Speakers|url=http://www.randi.org/site/index.php/component/content/article/37-static/448-the-amazing-meeting-7-speakers.html|accessdate=4 February 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=The Amaz!ng Meeting 7 Events|url=http://archive.randi.org/site/index.php/component/content/article/37-static/449-the-amazing-meeting-7-events.html|accessdate=4 January 2019}}</ref>  || 1100+<ref name=\"sfweekly\"/>\n|-\n|Oct 3-4, 2009 || Mermaid Conference Centre, Blackfriars, London, UK||TAM London|| [[Ja